### Lazy Loading Images

Lazy loading images is a common technique to improve page performance by delaying the loading of images until they are about to enter the viewport. This prevents unnecessary network requests and reduces initial page load time.

```
function lazyLoadImages() {
const images = document.querySelectorAll('img.lazy');
for (const img of images) {
if (isInViewport(img)) {
img.src = img.src;
img.src = img.src;
}
};

```

